<item>
            <title>[DERBY-777] Hang in starting network server on Z/OS</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-777</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Hang is in the java library call java/io/InputStreamReader.getEncoding&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Looking at the Derby code, this call is used to get the default encoding as a String, however&lt;br/&gt;
the default encoding value is not required, the localization code can just use the constructors&lt;br/&gt;
that use default encoding. Will attach a 10.1 branch patch soon. See if this can work around&lt;br/&gt;
the hang in the java library.&lt;/p&gt;

